		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Etiquette in Japan</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub">&nbsp;&nbsp;(Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Customs_and_etiquette_of_Japan&amp;redirect=no" title="Customs and etiquette of Japan">Customs and etiquette of Japan</a>)</div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The code of <b><a href="/wiki/Etiquette" title="Etiquette">etiquette</a> in <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japan</a></b> governs the expectations of social <a href="/wiki/Behavior" title="Behavior">behavior</a> in the country and is considered very important. Many books instruct readers on its minutiae.</p>
<p>Some <a href="/wiki/Convention_(philosophy_and_social_sciences)" title="Convention (philosophy and social sciences)" class="mw-redirect">customs</a> here may be very regional practices, and thus may not exist in all regions of Japan. The following are generally accepted modern customs in Japan. Some customs have changed over the course of history.</p>
